<h2>What are teacher sets?</h2>

<p>There are two types of Teacher Sets:
<ul style="list-style: inherit; margin: 5px 20px;">
  <li><a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?type%5B%5D=multi">Topic Sets</a> (10-30 copies of multiple titles on a single topic, such as <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?keyword=newbery%20award">Newbery Award Winners</a>)</li>
  <li><a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?type%5B%5D=single">Book Club Sets</a> (10 copies of a single title, such as <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets/20025726052907">The Fault in Our Stars</a>)</li>
</ul>
Teacher Sets are curated collections of items based on subjects or individual titles. You can search for Teacher Sets by grade band, subject, topic, and keyword.</p>
<p>Teacher Set subjects include <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?subject%5B%5D=English%2BLanguage%2BArts">English Language Arts</a>, <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?subject%5B%5D=Spanish%2BLanguage%2BArts">Spanish Language Arts</a>, <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?subject%5B%5D=Math">Math</a>, <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?subject%5B%5D=Science">Science</a>, <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?subject%5B%5D=Social%2BStudies">Social Studies</a>, and the <a href="http://sets.mylibrarynyc.org/app#/teacher_sets?subject%5B%5D=Arts">Arts</a>.</p>

