<h2>What Is the Teacher Sets Catalog?</h2>
<p><%= link_to "sets.mylibrarynyc.org", root_url %>, also known as the Teacher Sets web app, is a simplified way to find and order Teacher Sets for delivery to your school.</p>
<p>To order individual titles from your local library, go to <a href="http://www.mylibrarynyc.org/">mylibrarynyc.org</a> and click on Request Individual Items.</p>

<hr />

<h2>How Do I Use the Teacher Sets Catalog?</h2>
<p>To use the Teacher Sets catalog, all you need is your DOE email address. Once you confirm your school, you are registered and can place orders. If you do not check your DOE email frequently, you can provide an alternate email address to ensure that you receive order confirmations and updates in a timely manner.</p>

<hr />

<h2>Which Devices/Browsers Can I Use to Order Teacher Sets?</h2>
<p>You can order Teacher Sets from school or home using your internet-connected desktop/laptop (PC or Mac) or tablet/smartphone (Android or iOS). The Teacher Sets Catalog works best on Chrome, Safari, Firefox, and Opera browsers. You may encounter display or time-out issues using Internet Explorer.</p>

<hr />

<h2>What Happens After I Place an Order?</h2>
<p>Order confirmation, status update, and shipment notices are sent via email. They are also available under My Accounts. You may cancel an order the time it is placed or through the confirmation email. If a Teacher Set that you have ordered becomes unavailable, you will be notified within 24 hours (Monday-Friday). Teachers Sets are shipped, via UPS, on Fridays and are delivered directly to your school library. There is no charge for shipping or returns. The average delivery time for an available Teacher Set is 2 weeks.</p>

